    "filename": "/app/applet/godmode_themed/scripts/session-snapshot-protocolmd",
    "content": "# Unified Session Protocol\n\n## End of Session Prompt Template\nPaste this at the end of every Claude or AI Studio session when you hit a limit or are wrapping up:\n\n```text\nBefore this session ends — give me a Session Snapshot for this project.\nFormat the output EXACTLY as a single JSON object with the following keys. Do not include extra conversational text outside the JSON block.\n\n{\n  \"project\": \"project_name_here\",\n  \"summary\": \"Brief explanation of what was built or decided.\",\n  \"files_touched\": [\"file1.ts\", \"file2.tsx\"],\n  \"key_decisions\": \"Exact locked-in logic, e.g. distinct hand paths for hooks/uppercuts and impact scaling logic\",\n  \"next_target\": \"Exact concrete step to start the next session with\"\n}\n```\n\n## How to Export\n1. Install [Tampermonkey](https://www.tampermonkey.net/) in your browser.\n2. Create a new script and copy/paste the contents of `/scripts/tampermonkey-session-export.js`.\n3. Save the script.\n4. When Claude/Gemini generates the JSON from the prompt above:\n   a. **Copy the JSON block to your clipboard**.\n   b. Click the **\"⚡ Export to God-Mode OS\"** button that appears in the bottom right corner of Claude or AI Studio.\n5. The script will read your clipboard and send it directly to your God-Mode OS backend (`/api/godmode/session-export`), saving it into the `godmode_unified_sessions` SQLite table.\n\n## Start of Session Extraction\nWhen you start a new session, query your local database or check the Nexus UI. Provide the last session's `key_decisions` and `next_target` to the new AI context so it picks up exactly where the last one left off.\n"
